More than a month after 9-year old Leo Williams was shot in St Helena Bay - allegedly by a police officer - no arrests have been made. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - More than a month after nine-year-old Leo Williams was shot in St Helena Bay, allegedly by a police officer, no arrests have been made. The child sustained a head wound from a rubber bullet during a service delivery protest on 31 July. READ: Ipid probes another killing by police He died two weeks later in hospital. On Thursday, the Independent Police Investigative Directorate head visited his family on the West Coast.